race.comment: BRINDAVAN (2) appreciated the drop in grade and won in great style over the mile at Doomben last start, coming from well back to just arrive in time. That followed a 32-day break so there is plenty of improvement to come, particularly out to this trip on a bigger track. THAT'S MOLLY (4) was only beaten three lengths in Listed company two back then struggled to run a strong 2050m last time out. Nicely in after the claim and this is a much more suitable assignment. Big chance on an eight-day back-up. NOBLE CONQUEROR (7) tried hard but found BRINDAVAN a bit too good when they clashed at Doomben recently. Stormed home to win here at this trip two back. Cannot be left out of calculations. Veteran WAPITI (3) is back in a more suitable race today and can improve.
